cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

The paper deals with reachability analysis of continuous-time systems, which is a topic in control theory and robotics. Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.RO (Robotics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses sensitivity analysis and mixed monotonicity, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and optimization, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper includes numerical examples on traffic networks and satellite orbits, which could fall under cs.NE (Networks and Internet Architecture).
